    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-03T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="739"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1142c</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-03T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1291. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>
                    [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 134. Also for <persName>Smith</persName>. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DNH1">Norman H. Davis</persName> of the
                    Treasury Department expects to arrive in Madrid soon after July 15 in connection
                    with exchange matters. The Department and War Trade Board think it advisable to
                    defer the conclusion of the tonnage negotiations and the making of any definite
                    commitment until the <pb facs="0853" n="1687" xml:id="pg_1687"/> arrival of
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>, as we are
                    anxious to facilitate in every way possible the Treasury negotiations along with
                    our own. Please co-operate to fullest extent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
